### Summary

This document is an "IBM Batch Report" PDF, specifically for Batch Number 16, originating from the Bangor Vote Collection Point (ID 2178) in NSW, relating to Electoral Event ID 19694. The batch was created on June 10, 2016, and the report generated on June 15, 2016. It details the processing outcomes for 50 individual ballots within this batch. For each ballot, the report provides results across numerous verification categories, including Quality Assurance, Initials, Official Mark, Unusual Markings, Formality Result, Verification Action, Formality Reason, and various Above-the-Line (ATL) and Below-the-Line (BTL) preference checks (e.g., preferences, mismatches, saved, breakdown, formal status). The overwhelming majority of checks for all ballots indicate "OK," signifying successful processing. However, one specific entry for Ballot Number 2 shows "HAS ISSUES" under the `Formality Reason Checked` column, accompanied by the alphanumeric code `['O1 ']`, indicating a detected anomaly.

### Relevance to FOI Request

This document is directly relevant to Vanessa Teague's FOI request [LEX540] for 'IBM Outputs' from 2016. It is one of the "IBM Batch Report" PDF files sought, aligning with the specified dates (June 2016) and content type. It provides the detailed ballot-level insights into processing, including batch metadata (Vote Collection Point, Batch Number, Electoral Event ID), as outlined in the request overview. Crucially, the document exemplifies the presence of "HAS ISSUES" entries, specifically the `['O1 ']` code under `Formality Reason Checked` for Ballot 2. This directly corroborates the FOI request's mention that `Formality Reason Checked` often shows "HAS ISSUES" entries accompanied by alphanumeric codes, providing concrete evidence of the types of anomalies and exceptions tracked during ballot processing.
